### SP 800-171 Revision 3 Requirement 3.1.8 (03.01.08)
When the maximum number of consecutive invalid logon attempts is exceeded, requirement 3.1.8 requires the system to automatically perform one or more of the following selected actions [2]:
* Lock the account or node for an [Assignment: organization-defined time period] [2];
* Lock the account or node until released by an administrator [2];
* Delay the next logon prompt [2];
* Notify the system administrator [2]; or
* Take other action [2].

### SP 800-171 Revision 3 Requirement 3.2.1 (03.02.01)
Requirement 3.2.1 requires organizations to provide security literacy training to system users [7]:
* As part of initial training for new users and at an [Assignment: organization-defined frequency] thereafter [7];
* When required by system changes or following [Assignment: organization-defined events] [7]; and
* On recognizing and reporting indicators of insider threat, social engineering, and social mining [7].

Based on the provided excerpts, the three security objectives defined by FIPS 199 are:
1. Confidentiality [1][2]
2. Integrity [1][2]
3. Availability [1][2]

Regarding insider threat recognition training, SP 800-171 Revision 3 requires organizations to provide security literacy training to system users on recognizing and reporting indicators of insider threat [12]. This training must cover potential indicators and possible precursors of insider threats, which include behaviors such as:
* Inordinate, long-term job dissatisfaction [12];
* Attempts to gain access to information that is not required for job performance [12];
* Unexplained access to financial resources [12];
* Sexual harassment or bullying of fellow employees [12];
* Workplace violence [12]; and
* Other serious violations of the policies, procedures, rules, directives, or practices of organizations [12].
